<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Thanks to <a href="/u/ben_bai">u/ben_bai</a> there is a new 3.3.1.0 release of lwjgl3 for OpenBSD.</p> <p>I&#39;ve been testing it with 1.19.2, 1.19.4 and 1.20.</p> <p>I&#39;ve sent an update for the ports tree <a href="https://marc.info/?l=openbsd-ports&amp;m=168653020226980&amp;w=2">here</a></p> <p>I did the update and testing on -current, but I don&#39;t see any reason why one couldn&#39;t apply the patch to 7.3. If folks do some testing I might be convinced to commit the update to -stable</p> <p>(edit: Added notes about -current and -stable)</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/kmos-ports"> /u/kmos-ports </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/openbsd_gaming/comments/147fz4k/new_version_of_lwjgl3_available_plays_minecraft/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/openbsd_gaming/comments/147fz4k/new_version_of_lwjgl3_available_plays_minecraft/">[comments]</a></span>